I don't have a reason to remove stars. Everything about the restaurant is inviting. We sat where we pleased and were attended to immediately by a waitress that looked pretty sharp. We had several questions about the menu. She explained in both English and Spanish fluently. We had the Hauraches and Sopes and then realized that everything in store is made from scratch. Their portions are moderate and aren't heaps of food which is great considering everything is made from scratch. Their drinks, however, are enormous and are served in cute jars. We tried Cecina that day, a type of dried and ironed steak grilled with oil. It resembles gyro meat and salted and peppered. They do accept both cards and cash. They have a ten dollar minimum for cards. My girl and I both had two items off the menu and two large drinks adding up to somewhere around twenty-seven dollars. It's in front of a forked avenue so parking would have to be on a side street around the block. It's accessible on foot but probably awkward to wheelchairs without help. I remember seeing a guy with an oxygen tank walk in with some help from what I assume was his daughter. The restroom is bright, REALLY CLEAN, and handicap friendly. This place is wonderful if you're looking for some authentic Mexican food with full service. The flavors are full on and the store does not try to pass as a quick-bite diner.
